From: Anjali Singhai Jain <anjali.singhai@intel.com>
Date: Tue, 31 Mar 2015 00:45:01 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 274/285] i40e: Print some more info to help figure out the
 cause of HMC error

commit 25fc0e6590d7c18886cab667430c0da16f0586c4
https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/davem/net-next.git

HMC_ERRORINFO and HMC_ERRORDATA helps explain the cause of HMC error.

Change-ID: I053bbc175a5f4c5c3e9ec2ea7400d5c56aaa4ec1
Signed-off-by: Anjali Singhai Jain <anjali.singhai@intel.com>
Tested-by: Jim Young <james.m.young@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Jeff Kirsher <jeffrey.t.kirsher@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Pengyu Ma <pengyu.ma@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/intel/i40e/i40e_main.c |    3 +++
 1 files changed, 3 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/i40e/i40e_main.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/i40e/i40e_main.c
index 35fe312..e3c110b 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/i40e/i40e_main.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/i40e/i40e_main.c
@@ -3192,6 +3192,9 @@ static irqreturn_t i40e_intr(int irq, void *data)
 	if (icr0 & I40E_PFINT_ICR0_HMC_ERR_MASK) {
 		icr0 &= ~I40E_PFINT_ICR0_HMC_ERR_MASK;
 		dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "HMC error interrupt\n");
+		dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "HMC error info 0x%x, HMC error data 0x%x\n",
+			 rd32(hw, I40E_PFHMC_ERRORINFO),
+			 rd32(hw, I40E_PFHMC_ERRORDATA));
 	}
 
 	if (icr0 & I40E_PFINT_ICR0_TIMESYNC_MASK) {
